  "title": "Expand hierarchicalMenu root item",
  "body": "By default, hierarchicalMenu items are collapsed and user has to click any item to see sub-items as you can see in below screenshot that _Category_ **Electric & Electronic** item collapsed.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"278\" alt=\"screen shot 2017-09-20 at 1 43 54 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/56748/30638051-396eca46-9e0b-11e7-862d-f052352fd793.png\">\r\n\r\nBut as it is the only one root item(which has sub-items) so I want to expand it as soon as page loads so that user don't need to click on the item to see sub-items as below screenshot.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"275\" alt=\"screen shot 2017-09-20 at 1 41 59 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/56748/30638070-4690b0f4-9e0b-11e7-8dfe-8a91f61c65a8.png\">\r\n\r\nHere is the page: https://protenders.com/companies/bodet/products\r\n\r\nIs it possible?",
